The paper discusses supervised hashing methods for optimizing retrieval speed and storage cost while preserving semantic information, which is a common problem in computer vision (CV) and information retrieval (IR). The paper also mentions the use of conditional random fields (CRF), which is a popular machine learning (ML) technique used in natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV). The paper proposes two new methods based on energy minimization, which is a common optimization technique in machine learning (ML) and computer science (CS) in general. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.CV, cs.LG, and cs.IR, followed by cs.MM and cs.CL.
